==English==

===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|la|interstitium|}}, from {{m|la|inter||between}} + {{m|la|sistō|t=to stand, place}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˌɪntɚˈstɪʃi.əm/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|interstitia}}

# {{lb|en|medicine}} An [[interstitial]] space within a tissue or organ.
# {{lb|en|medicine}} Specifically the tissue between the pulmonary [[alveoli]] and the bloodstream.
# {{lb|en|philosophy}} A state between systems or spaces.
# An [[interstice]], the interval of time required by the Roman [[Catholic]] [[Church]] between the attainment of different degrees of an order (pluralised as ''interstitia'' for the overall policy, which is also occasionally spelled ''instertitia'').

